Privacy Policy for Eva's Wardrobe Android Application

Effective Date: 5 July 2023

At Eva's Wardrobe, we value your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and safeguard the information you provide when you use our Android application. Please read this policy carefully to understand our practices regarding your personal data.

1. Information We Collect
1.1 Personal Information
We do not collect any personally identifiable information (PII) such as your name, address, email address, or phone number through Eva's Wardrobe Android application.

1.2 Non-Personal Information
We may collect non-personal information when you use Eva's Wardrobe, such as your device's unique identifier (e.g., Android Advertising ID), IP address, device model, operating system version, and usage statistics. This information is collected solely for analytical purposes to improve our application and user experience.

2. Use of Information
2.1 Advertisements
Eva's Wardrobe integrates AdMob, a mobile advertising platform provided by Google. AdMob may collect and use non-personal information about your device to provide personalized advertisements within our application. Please review the AdMob Privacy Policy for more information on their data collection and usage practices.

2.2 Analytics
We may use third-party analytics tools to gather and analyze non-personal information about how users interact with Eva's Wardrobe. This helps us understand user behavior, preferences, and usage patterns to improve our application's performance, features, and content.

3. Data Sharing and Disclosure
We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your information to third parties for marketing or advertising purposes. However, we may share non-personal information with trusted third-party service providers that assist us in operating and improving our application. These third parties are bound by strict confidentiality agreements and are prohibited from using your information for any purpose other than assisting us.

4. Data Security
We take reasonable measures to protect the information we collect within Eva's Wardrobe against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. However, please note that no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

5. Children's Privacy
Eva's Wardrobe does not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13. If you believe we have inadvertently collected information from a child, please contact us at the email provided below, and we will promptly remove the information from our records.

6. Changes to this Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to modify or update this Privacy Policy at any time. Any changes will be effective immediately upon posting the updated policy within Eva's Wardrobe. We encourage you to review this policy periodically for any updates.

7. Contact Us
If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or the privacy practices related to Eva's Wardrobe, please contact us at:

Email: mail@evaswardrobe.com

Please allow us a reasonable time to respond to your inquiries.

By using Eva's Wardrobe, you agree to the terms and conditions outlined in this Privacy Policy.

Last updated: 5 July 2023
